data.title: Palm Beach Preservation Foundation
data.meta_description: The Preservation Foundation of Palm Beach is a private, nonprofit membership organization dedicated to the preservation of the historic, architectural, and cultural heritage of Palm Beach, Florida. Through advocacy initiatives, educational programs, architectural resources, and cultural events, the Foundation’s goal is to encourage the community to learn about and save the historic buildings that truly make Palm Beach special.
data.text:
Knowledge. Stewardship. Culture.

Body

The Preservation Foundation of Palm Beach protects and celebrates the architectural, botanical, and cultural heritage of Palm Beach. Through advocacy initiatives, educational programs, architectural resources, and cultural events, the Foundation’s goal is to inspire the community to learn about and protect the places that make Palm Beach special.

Awards

The Preservation Foundation’s prestigious awards recognize dedicated property owners and leading architects each year for projects that preserve the character and traditions of Palm Beach.

Robert I. Ballinger Award

Polly Earl Award

Elizabeth L. and John H. Schuler Award

Lesly S. Smith Landscape Award

Edward E. and Suzanne G. Elson Award
